We can reverse aging. To make it happen, we have to remember that death is simply bad.

We took this picture after receiving our first major grant, four years ago. 

In the underground parking of our student housing. I don't think the car belonged to one of the students though.

We meant to send the picture along with the "thank you" mail to the guys on the other side of the planet who believed in us. 

Imagining all the ways in which it might not be funny, we didn't. So here it is now. It's aged well. 

We still have no intentions of buying Maseratis, Max' hair is much more grey and mine gone. 

I hope Matt and Nick are happy that their trust led to much more exciting stuff coming out of EA Geneva. 

And I'm grateful to still be just as excited as when I read that confirmation email. We've handed over EA Geneva into qualified hands and are now building up the Simon Institute for Longterm Governance.

If you want more pictures of us next to sportscars, get in touch to discuss your tax deductible donation ;)
